==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Propulsion
<hw>Pro*pul"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>propulsion</ets>. See <er>Propel</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
act driving forward or away; the act or process of propelling; <as>as,
steam <ex>propulsion</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An impelling act or movement.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>God works in all things; all obey⟦br⟧
His first <qex>propulsion</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Whittier.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Propulsive</ent>⟦br⟧
